race.comment: SHAQUE D'AMOUR (22) has been in the money five times from 14 runs with all of the placings coming at Ipswich. Ran a cheeky race at mammoth odds last time out at Doomben. Draws the fence and is sure to be prominent for a long way. VILLANDRY (19) returned with a real eye-catcher recently over 1050m at Rockhampton, coming from last at one stage to be beaten in a three-way go. Major player over the extra trip with added fitness. ICYMISS (12) has been just behind the placegetters at both runs to date. Nicely drawn and with improvement to come is one of the key runners. ROCKABILLY (5) is back from a five-month spell. Placed two from two in the maiden prep and has trialled well leading into this. LAVARACK (1) is a first starter by Bivouac from the Gollan yard. Trial form nothing to write home about but the markets says he is ready to run well.
